The paper deals with recommendation systems, which are typically studied in the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of content features and metadata to improve recommendations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of semantic embeddings suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
